timeline_data.body:
Pasting my comment from an internal issue here:

There seems to be a every small timing hole in the hashtable code:

```
hashTableFind(J9HashTable *table, void *entry)
{
...
    if (NULL == table->listNodePool) {
        void **node = hashTableFindNodeSpaceOpt(table, entry, head);
        findNode = (NULL != *node) ? node : NULL;              <--------------- *node is not NULL
...
    return findNode;
}


static void **
hashTableFindNodeSpaceOpt(J9HashTable *table, void *entry, void **head)
{
    void **node = head;
    while ((NULL != *node) && (0 == table->hashEqualFn(node, entry, table->equalFnUserData))) {
        node += 1;
        if (node == &table->nodes[table->tableSize]) {
            node = &table->nodes[0];
        }
    }
    return node;                                                <------------ *node is NULL
}
```

When returning from hashTableFindNodeSpaceOpt() node was pointing to NULL.
(another thread added a new hash entry at node)
After returned to hashTableFind(),  *node is not NULL, findNode is now pointing to the newly added J9Class.

Note fast hash is enabled, the reader does not take class table mutex here.

